result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony Tyrone Moore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal) [Modifiers: Repeater], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:00 AM DA calls cases: 22CF38, 22CF89, 22CF96, 22CF120, 22CF125 and states appearances. Defendant Anthony Tyrone Moore in court, in custody.  Attorney Karl J Kelz. in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Kelz states a global agreement has been reached and recites agreement on record. DA Kelz states case 22CF125 has not had an initial appearance. Attorney Kaupie will proceed with an initial appearance on this matter as that case is part of the Global Settlement. in case 22CF125 Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Preliminary Hearing waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court. Court finds probable cause exists that a crime was committed and binds DE over for trial in each case. Information filed, acknowledged by parties and reading waived.  In cases 22CF96, 22CF89, and 22CF38  Preliminary Hearings waived.  Waiver accepted by the Court.  Contingent upon the defendant's plea in cases 22CF38 and 22CF89 the State will move to Dismiss and read in all counts in cases: 22CF96, 22CF120, 22CF125. Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST to each count in cases: 22CF38 and 22CF89 therefore all counts in cases: 22CF96, 22CF120, and 22CF25 are DISMISSED and READ IN. Court questions DE regarding the plea. DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC. Comments by parties.
Court Imposes:

(22CF96, 22CF38, New case)

Kelz  in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Kaupie makes statements in regards to the defendant's non appearance at the last initial appearance in case 22CF96 and a preliminary hearing in case 22CF38. Attorney Kaupie request bond be re-instated and an initial appearance happen in case 22CF96. Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled. Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. Return on warrant on August 23, 2022 at 10:00 am.
